Quality assurance exists to prevent negative experiences that software does not work.

The role of QA exists to prevent problems in an application so that users don't encounter bugs and crashes.
Quality assurance -QA - a systematic process used to determine whether a product meets specifications 

An individual in the QA role constantly questions parts of the software development process to ensure the team is building the right product and building it correctly. 
A QA's primary goal should be to help their team move quickly with confidence. They establish and maintain standards 